ry\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Troubleshooting test failures**\\n\\nI need to fix a failing existing test related to the experimental property as it seems Byte Buddy's OpenedClassReader might be reading the static EXPERIMENTAL from the system property too early. The failure occurs in UnsafeOverride.make while generating classes. The original issue stems from ClassInjector, not my new test. The user inquires about the error following my changes. I think we should modify the test to correctly handle the IllegalArgumentException if the message indicates an experimental issue, while ensuring not to assert on a broken version-specific failure path.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Configuring JVM test properties**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need to add `jvmArgs` for my JVM test. I can configure Gradle with something like `-Dorg.modelmapper.internal.bytebuddy.experimental=true`, but what about the native test runtime? It seems the existing test sets that property at the method start, but it might be initialized too early since OpenedClassReader could do that beforehand. I’m thinking maybe setting the system property globally for all test tasks would be better. Setting the experimental property seems a bit risky, but it's meant for testing the experimental path. It needs to be applied before JVM startup for it to take effect.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing Gradle structure**\\n\\nI need to check the structure of `build.gradle` in other tests, specifically looking for how they set the `systemProperty`. This could give me insights into best practices or common patterns for configuring properties in the test environment. Understanding how other tests handle this might help me figure out the right approach for my current task. It’s worth taking the time to ensure everything is set up correctly to avoid potential pitfalls!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_hwo1Gh62jKI2zkgPDJohhtdW|fc_0a026d27173957b2016a25472e43f8819494f