[thinking] **Exploring subprocess options**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering running a subprocess with JDK21, but I need to check if JAVA_HOME is set up correctly. I’m thinking about testing both under native and Java environments, and whether the external process is public. Another angle is covering dynamic access—could the dynamic access reporter instrument the current process to ensure everything works as intended? There’s a lot to consider, so I want to be thorough to get it right!
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Explaining the uncovered call site**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I see that the task indicates if there's a remaining call site only reachable through a broken or unsupported method, I should leave it uncovered. It seems I might not need any edits, since the active class still has one uncovered aspect. I can mention, "I left it uncovered." We've already conducted the relevant test and ensured Gradle support, so I think I'll clarify that no code changes were made in this round.
