one, and `System.getSecurityManager()` remains `null`. The existing `activeSecurityManagerChecksDispatcherCreationPermissionWhenSupported()` test already exercises this path on runtimes where installing a `SecurityManager` is still supported, and `build.gradle` now enables that supported path for pre-Java-24 runs with:\n\n```groovy\n-Djava.security.manager=allow\n```\n\nSo the remaining call site is not reachable through supported behavior on the active Java 25 runtime. Covering it would require forcing internal JDK state or another unsupported Security Manager workaround, which would violate the task rules.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a026d27173957b2016a254976e16481949b2ba4b354ed8ea3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 380, "output": 2283, "cacheRead": 60416, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 63079, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780828480202, "responseId": "resp_0a026d27173957b2016a25494145a4819489c80648dd125dbe"}, "toolResults": []}
